@justinkterry Before I go willy-nilly merging again, does this help you?

When using the DRF decorator like @api_view, django passes an instance of rest_framework.request.Request and not an instance of HttpRequest, so I updated the if the statement to work with it.

```
@api_view(['POST'])
@permission_classes((IsAuthenticated,))
@ratelimit(key='user', rate='100/h')
def emailReceipts(request):
    pass
```

I was using truffle and kept getting

{"error": {"message": "Server error:   File \"/usr/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/testrpc/testrpc.py\", line 291, in eth_compileSolidity | KeyError: 0", "code": -32603}, "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 1}

This fixed it for me

Json objects are ordered, python dicts are not, which will cause code depending on ordering eg. 
{
 'name': 'joe',
 'surname': 'bloggs'
}

to sometimes output surname first if it just iterated through the key/values.

Pending review from @mbruggmann...  I think the intention of the mocks originally was to test the complete checks for his new `bulk_complete` in isolation without actually having to request the API.

We do seem to need an actual client on the relevant integration tests, however.  This should fix [the errors in the build](https://travis-ci.org/spotify/luigi/jobs/92593476#L208) for gcloud environment.

@Tarrasch @econchick

The IPv4 Unicast EOR messages were being serialized into invalid JSON across the API.  They were also being incorrectly serialized as an NLRI within an announce which differs from the encoding of EOR in all other AFIs/SAFIs so this embedding seems unintentional.

This patch set fixes the structure of the IPv4 unicast EOR to match the other families.  It also ensures that the string encoding of these EORs is provided over the API.  AFI/SAFI was being encoded as ints.

Old IPv4 EOR (invalid json, ints for AFI/SAFI)
```
...
		"message": {
			"update": {
				"announce": {
					"1 1": {
						"null": ["eor": {
							"afi": "1",
							"safi": "1"
						}]
					}
				}
			}
		}
...
```

New IPv4 EOR (valid json, strings for AFI/SAFI)
```
...
        "message": {
            "eor": {
                "afi": "ipv4", 
                "safi": "unicast"
            }
        }
...
```

IPv6 EOR for reference (unchanged in this patch set)
```
...
        "message": {
            "eor": {
                "afi": "ipv6", 
                "safi": "unicast"
            }
        }
...
```

