RFD child should keep attached to its parent when the parent forms/joins a new partition without changing routerid - new round of attach process should be avoided

Besides, choose a random initial mRouterIdSequence when forming a new partition as the spec says.

@jwhui would you please help to review it?

This PR is to resolve #460.  Main thoughts about this Autopend feature:
1) Assume Phy layer support AutoPend and Source Match by default.

2) Mac layer only provides two interfaces to allow upper layer add address to Phy layer source match table per packet destined to SED and remove the address after the packet is delivered.
```
ThreadError AddSrcMatchAddressEntry(Address &aAddr);
ThreadError ClearSrcMatchAddressEntry(Address &aAddr);
```

3) Phy layer provides four interfaces to all Mac layer to add/remove short/extended address to the source match table.
```
ThreadError otPlatRadioAddShortSrcMatchAddressEntry(uint16_t aShortAddress, uint16_t aPanId);
ThreadError otPlatRadioAddExtSrcMatchAddressEntry(uint8_t *aExtAddress);
ThreadError otPlatRadioClearShortSrcMatchAddressEntry(uint16_t aShortAddress, uint16_t aPanId);
ThreadError otPlatRadioClearExtSrcMatchAddressEntry(uint8_t *aExtAddress);
```

4) Phy layer would automatically ack with FramePending set only for data poll packets when there is packets queued for SED normally. But if the queued messages for SEDs are more than the entries of the source match table, the radio would ack with FramePending set for all packets.
eg for CC2538, the maximum entries of the source match table is 24.

Theses interfaces are open to change if there are more requirements.

Below is the harness output with Harness Release 19.0
[Router_5_3_2.zip](https://github.com/openthread/openthread/files/466671/Router_5_3_2.zip)

